      "message": "Edwin, if you don\u0027t mind I would like to share with you a perhaps more general code design feedback, upon seeing this class: \n\nIt\u0027s normally considered much better design to not write C like code with static methods taking a ton of arguments, like this one here, but think about which of these arguments are \"dependent services\" (stuff you need to do the work in this method; like DataBroker, IdManagerService, IMdsalApiManager) -VS- the \"real\" arguments this method needs (InstanceIdentifier, String etc.).  You should keep the former as (final) fields, with a @Inject constructor, and then @Inejct this @Singleton where oyu need it.  I suspect you may think that is overhead ;) but it does make code like this a bit simpler and more harmonious with how we generally (should.. :) write code everywhere.\n\nYou would then typically also make something like the ManagedNewTransactionRunner a field of the class, instead of new it in the method (and assign it in the constructor).\n\nThe other question of course is if we need such a class at all, or instead want to put this single method into some other existing class (which should also be designed as suggested above) - I\u0027ll have to leave that up to you.",
